Dr. Zeiders (picture attached) Bio:
Dr. Gregory Zeiders is a board-certified orthopedic surgeon and Fellow of both the American Osteopathic Academy of Orthopedics (FAOAO) and the American Academy of Orthopaedic Surgeons (FAAOS). He specializes in trauma, fracture care, deformity correction, and arthroscopic surgery, and founded Zeiders Orthopedics PLLC in Oklahoma City to provide advanced, personalized care for patients with bone, joint, and sports-related injuries.
Originally from Bartlesville, Oklahoma, Dr. Zeiders competed in gymnastics at the University of Oklahoma before pursuing his medical degree at Oklahoma State University College of Osteopathic Medicine. He completed advanced fellowship training in both the U.S. and Australia, with a focus on complex orthopedic trauma and reconstruction.
For the past 13 years, Dr. Zeiders has served as an oral board certification and board defense examiner for the American Osteopathic Academy of Orthopedics, helping shape and uphold the standards of the specialty. In addition, he has worked with the Academy Fellowship Committee for the last 5 years as well as a consultant and researcher with multiple orthopedic companies, contributing to innovation in fracture management, implants, and surgical techniques.
Beyond his surgical practice, Dr. Zeiders has published research, taught medical students and residents, and served as Chief of Surgery at the University of Oklahoma Medical Center–Edmond. He also supports athletes as a physician for the Nadia Comaneci International Gymnastics Tournament.
When he’s not in the operating room, Dr. Zeiders enjoys spending time with his three sons and his large extended family.
